## Planes y capacidades

### Planes del assistant

| Plan | Precio/mes | Precio/año |
|---|---|---|
| Free | $0 | — |
| Pro | $4 | $38.40 |
| Premium | $5 | $48 |

Estrategia de señuelo: Pro a $4 tiene límites significativos; Premium a $5 (solo $1 más) es casi ilimitado.

### Usuarios de prueba

| Email | Plan | Password |
|---|---|---|
| `assistant-free@test.com` | Free | `password` |
| `assistant-pro@test.com` | Pro | `password` |
| `assistant-premium@test.com` | Premium | `password` |

Seeder: `AssistantPlanSeeder` + `AssistantUserSeeder`. Los usuarios de assistant no tienen producto `core`.

### Límites completos (en `limits_json`)

| Clave | Tipo | Free | Pro | Premium |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `messages_daily` | daily | 15 | 60 | ∞ |
| `memory_total` | permanent | 15 | 60 | ∞ |
| `memory_categories` | permanent | 2 | 5 | ∞ |
| `friends` | permanent | 5 | 30 | ∞ |
| `friend_categories` | permanent | 2 | 5 | ∞ |
| `lists` | permanent | 3 | 15 | ∞ |
| `list_items_max` | permanent | 15 | 50 | ∞ |
| `events_monthly` | monthly | 20 | 100 | ∞ |
| `reminders_active` | permanent | 3 | 15 | ∞ |
| `context_messages` | permanent | 20 | 60 | 200 |
| `storage_mb` | permanent | 0 | 2048 | 20480 |
| `upload_monthly_mb` | monthly | 0 | 512 | 4096 |
| `upload_max_mb` | permanent | 0 | 20 | 50 |
| `expenses_enabled` | boolean | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
| `custom_instructions` | boolean | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ |
| `export_enabled` | boolean | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |

### `useAssistantCapabilities`

`composables/assistant/useAssistantCapabilities.ts` — lee `session.enterprise.products.assistant.limits` estáticamente y expone variables nombradas:

```ts
const { canUploadFiles, messagesDaily, storageMb, isPremium, ... } = useAssistantCapabilities()
```

Variables booleanas: `canUploadFiles`, `canUseExpenses`, `canUseCustomInstructions`, `canExport`, `isPro`, `isPremium`, `isPaid`.
Variables numéricas: `messagesDaily`, `memoryTotal`, `storagesMb`, `uploadMonthlyMb`, `uploadMaxMb`, etc.

### `useAppsEnabled`

`composables/core/useAppsEnabled.ts` — lee `session.enterprise.products` y expone:

```ts
const { hasAssistant, hasCore } = useAppsEnabled()
```

`AppMenuSwitcher` filtra las apps visibles según el producto que requiere cada ruta (`meta.appProduct`). Un usuario solo-assistant no ve Workspaces ni Image Studio.

